==English==

===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} [[κάθεξις]] ''(kathexis,''  [[holding]], [[retention]]). Entered English language as a translation for the common everyday German word ''Besetzung'', which in this context means "occupation" in the sense of a position or something being occupied or filled, and not a military occupation of a place or the filling of job positions (although it can also mean either of these in other contexts). In English translations, a Greek word was used to be more scientific.

===Noun===
'''cathexis'''
#(''Freudian psychology'') the [[concentration]] of [[libido]] or [[emotional]] [[energy]] on a single object or idea

